 ;; The load-bearing typed holes the construction had to discharge (the 6 failure modes = the HARD parts).
 ;; Grading is honest: F1/F3/F4/F5 have isolated unit tests; F2/F6 are structural (verified by inspection,
 ;; no isolated unit test) — graded :discharged-by with an explicit :verified note, NOT fabricated tests.
 :typed-holes
 [{:at :F1-server-initiated-liveness
   :wanted "the server must PROBE clients, not merely PONG-reply — a half-open TCP (sleep/wake, WiFi→ethernet) leaves a zombie nick receiving into the void; ANY received line (not just PONG) must reset liveness, and idle clients past the timeout must be reaped"
   :discharged-by "6ce7ad7 (keepalive-loop single future → reap-dead! + ping-idle!; touch! on every :on-line; :last-activity-at/:ping-pending? client state; ping-interval 30s / ping-timeout 90s)"
   :verified "7 tests §11 (ping-after-interval, not-to-active, pong-clears-pending, any-message-resets, reap-removes/preserves, reap-emits-evidence)"}
  {:at :F2-bounded-read
   :wanted ".readLine() must not block forever on a stalled half-open socket (each stall permanently leaks one thread + one socket); a read timeout must fire, and a bare SocketTimeoutException must be distinguished from a real error (keepalive reaps, reader does not treat it as disconnect-error)"
   :discharged-by "6ce7ad7 ((.setSoTimeout socket 120000) in accept loop; reader (catch SocketTimeoutException _ nil) separate from (catch Exception e …emit-error-evidence!))"
   :verified :inspection                  ; structural — no isolated unit test (timing-dependent); confirmed in code
   :note "socket-timeout-ms configurable; SO_TIMEOUT set BEFORE reader/writer construction"}
  {:at :F3-no-silent-swallow
   :wanted "every (catch Exception _) must be replaced so NO exception is silently discarded — reader-loop, send-fn, relay, accept, keepalive, send-to-channel all surface a :tension evidence entry; errors must surface at the layer that caused them (realtime/loop-failure-signals)"
   :discharged-by "6ce7ad7 (emit-error-evidence! at all catch sites: reader-error, send-error, relay-timeout, relay-error, keepalive-error, accept-error, keepalive-reap) — later hardened: bac7422 re-routed the sink estore/append* → evidence.boundary/append! (single-boundary)"
   :verified "1 test §14 (send-errors-logged-to-evidence) + reap-emits-evidence §11 + relay-timeout-emits-evidence §13"}
  {:at :F4-ghost-nick-reclaim
   :wanted "a reconnecting client (ERC auto-reconnect after a blip) must reclaim its nick from the stale ghost entry, else nick-collision or coexisting entries cause duplicate/missing messages; but a LIVE collision must still return ERR_NICKNAMEINUSE (433) — ghost-ness is decided by the F1 liveness timer, not guessed"
   :discharged-by "6ce7ad7 (nick-ghost? = :ping-pending? OR elapsed > ping-timeout-ms; kill-ghost! QUITs + dissocs + close-fn; NICK handler reclaims-or-433) — later 1530126 fixed delivery after in-channel nick changes"
   :verified "3 tests §12 (nick-reclaim-from-ghost, nick-collision-for-live-client, ghost-detection-uses-timeout)"}
  {:at :F5-relay-head-of-line-blocking
   :wanted "relay-fn iterating agents and calling ws-send-fn SYNCHRONOUSLY means one stalled/slow/dead-but-undetected agent WS blocks every other agent in the channel from receiving; each per-agent send must have a deadline, stalls must be skipped and surfaced"
   :discharged-by "6ce7ad7 (per-agent (future (ws-send-fn …)) + (deref f relay-timeout-ms ::timeout) + future-cancel + :tension evidence on timeout; default 5000ms) — later 29d18a9/5298949/776e7c6 hardened deliverability/visibility of relay responses"
   :verified "2 tests §13 (relay-timeout-skips-stalled-agent, relay-timeout-emits-evidence)"}
  {:at :F6-clean-coordinated-shutdown
   :wanted "the accept loop spawns untracked reader futures; stop-fn closes writers but never joins/cancels readers or the keepalive future — orphaned threads survive shutdown; shutdown must stop EVERY thread and close EVERY socket"
   :discharged-by "6ce7ad7 (!reader-futures atom {client-id → future}; stop-fn (reset! !running false) + (future-cancel) over all reader futures + keepalive-loop + accept-loop + close all writers)"
   :verified :inspection                  ; structural — no isolated unit test (thread-lifecycle); confirmed in code
   :note "reader future self-removes from !reader-futures on exit; keepalive loop guards on @!running"}]

